Fourth Step: 

1. Login as ‘user1’ and perform below
su user1

2. Create directory – “/home/user2/dir1”
sudo mkdir /home/user2/dir1

3. Change to “/dir2/dir1/dir2/dir10” directory and create file “/opt/dir14/dir10/f1” using relative path method.

cd /dir2/dir1/dir2/dir10
cd ../../../../opt/dir14/dir10/
touch f1 

4. Move the file from “/opt/dir14/dir10/f1” to  user1 home directory
sudo mv /opt/dir14/dir10/f1 /home/user1
ls /home/user1

5. Delete the directory recursively “/dir4”
sudo rm -Rf /dir4

6. Delete all child files and directories under “/opt/dir14” using single command.
sudo rm -rf /opt/dir14/*

7. Write this text “Linux assessment for an DevOps Engineer!! Learn with Fun!!” to the /f3 file and save it.
sudo chown user2:user2 /f3
vi f3
i
write text
ecs :wq